{"key":"post-8967883","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>8967883</id>\n<content>I'd suggest cutting way more holes than you think you'll need, and then taping them back up if you're not able to hold humidity.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you run a coolmist 24/7, you'll flood your floor.&amp;nbsp; I used to use humidistats to control the humidity, but went back to timers after they kept getting clogged up with spores.&amp;nbsp; I have slits from floor to ceiling and run a humidifier one to two minutes on, six to ten minutes off, depending on ambient humidity and season.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Remember, the more fresh air, the better.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>8967924</next>\n<prev>8967742</prev>\n<first>8955438</first>\n<last>8968403</last>\n<when>1222106484</when>\n<utime>09/22/08 09:01 PM</utime>\n</post>"}